      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please do not make any changes to your medication without consulting your doctor first. Sertraline is a carefully balanced prescription drug, and abruptly stopping it or swapping it for St. John's Wort can cause serious withdrawal symptoms or dangerous interactions. St. John's Wort is known to interact negatively with many medications, including SSRIs, potentially leading to serotonin syndrome. Stick with your current dosage and let your physician manage the side effects; they can advise on tapering or adjusting your treatment plan safely.",
